_Mgmt.DirectRouting.List.Columns.Network: Column name for Network effectiveness for all stream in Current trunks table. It's value will look like {percentage network effectiveness value (number of streams taken for calculating %).
_Mgmt.DirectRouting.List.ColumnsDescript: Column description for Network effectiveness for all stream in Current trunks table. Its value will look like {percentage network effectiveness value (number of streams taken for calculating %).
Mgmt.DirectRouting.List.ColumnsDescripti: Network Effectiveness Ratio is ITU-T recommended parameter measure ability of the network to deliver calls. It is calculated based on the formula: 𝑁𝐸𝑅=𝐴𝑛𝑠𝑤𝑒𝑟𝑒𝑑 𝑐𝑎𝑙𝑙𝑠+𝑈𝑠𝑒𝑟 𝐵𝑢𝑠𝑦+𝑅𝑖𝑛𝑔 𝑛𝑜 𝐴𝑛𝑠𝑤𝑒𝑟+𝑇𝑒𝑟𝑚𝑖𝑛𝑎𝑙 𝑅𝑒𝑗𝑒𝑐𝑡𝑆𝑒𝑖𝑧𝑢𝑟𝑒𝑠𝑥100. The ratio calculates how many calls were delivered and ignores user related errors, such as unanswered calls or user rejected calls. If the value goes down it indicates that network has a problem that requires investigation.
_Mgmt.DirectRouting.List.Columns.Network: Value of Network effectiveness for all stream in Current trunks table. where {nerPerc} is percentage of network effectiveness value and {numberOfStreams} is number of streams taken for calculating %.
_Mgmt.DirectRouting.List.Columns.Average: Column name for Average call duration for all stream in Current trunks table. It's value will look like {call duration time in minutes or seconds (number of streams taken for calculation)
_Mgmt.DirectRouting.List.ColumnsDescript: Column description for Average call duration for all stream in Current trunks table. It's value will look like {call duration time in minutes or seconds (number of streams taken for calculation)
Mgmt.DirectRouting.List.ColumnsDescripti: Average Call Duration is a good indicator of the quality of end user experience. A decrease of Average Call duration value often indicates problems with calling experience (noise, glitches, delays, mid-call failures, and so on). If users experience issues with voice, they can start trying to redial the numbers several times or after a short call switch to a mobile device.
_Mgmt.DirectRouting.List.Columns.Average: Value of Average call duration for all stream in Current trunks table. where {callDurationMin} is call duration time in minutes and {numberOfStreams} is number of streams taken for calculation.
Value of Average call duration for all stream in Current trunks table. where {callDurationSec} is call duration time in seconds and {numberOfStreams} is number of streams taken for calculation.
_Mgmt.DirectRouting.List.Columns.TLSConn: Column name for TLS connectivity status in Current trunks table. It's value could be Active, No data or Warning.
_Mgmt.DirectRouting.List.ColumnsDescript: Column description for TLS connectivity status in Current trunks table. It's value could be Active, No data or Warning.
Mgmt.DirectRouting.List.ColumnsDescripti: Microsoft Phone System has several mechanisms to detect the health of the connected SBCs. SIP Options together with TLS Handshake Monitoring help to detect the issues on the application level. Imagine you have a trunk that can be reached on the network level by ping but certificate has expired, or SIP stack doesn't work. To identify the issues early, we highly recommend enabling sending SIP options to us. Please consult with SBC manufacturer documentation how to configure sending the SIP options.
_Mgmt.DirectRouting.List.Columns.SIPOpti: Column name for SIP options status in Current trunks table. It's value could be Active or Warning
_Mgmt.DirectRouting.List.Columns.Concurr: Column name for Concurrent call capacity in Current trunks table. It's value could be 'Within Limits', 'Capacity not set', '% of capacity used' and '100% out of capacity'
_Mgmt.DirectRouting.List.ColumnsDescript: Column description for Concurrent call capacity in Current trunks table. It's value could be 'Within Limits', 'Capacity not set', '% of capacity used' and '100% out of capacity'
Mgmt.DirectRouting.List.ColumnsDescripti: During the pairing, the organization administrator can specify the capacity of the connected trunk. Capacity is set in number of simultaneous calls that trunk can handle. Each SBC vendor provides this information. Please consult the SBC and trunk documentation and set the limit using Set-CSOnlinePSTNGateway. To get detailed instructions you can run “help Set-CSOnlinePSTNGateway -detailed. Setting the limit will help you to be notified when your trunk is near or crossed the existing capacity based on our statistics. Note we do not measure real utilization of hardware on SBC. We calculate number of concurrent calls and compare to the number configured in the command.

_Mgmt.DirectRouting.ConcurrentCallMoreTh: 'How to fix' text for when concurrent call% of trunk reaches 90%, where {maxConcurrentCallLimit} is maximum concurrent call limit set by tenant admin and {currentConcurrentCallValue} is current concurrent call trunk has been used.
Mgmt.DirectRouting.ConcurrentCallMoreTha: Each trunk has a limit of calls it can handle at a time. The current limit is {maxConcurrentCallLimit}. Your current call volume is consuming more than 95% of this limit. If you don’t expect call volume to increase, you can safely ignore this message and set the warning alert higher than {currentConcurrentCallValue}. If you expect increased call volume on this trunk, you need to add capacity to your Session Border Controller (SBC) or add additional SBCs to the route. Note: We don’t measure real-time volume on SBC. Instead, we calculate the number of concurrent calls based on statistics from the last 4 hours and compare it to the number configured during the pairing (New-CSOnlinePSTNGW, parameter -Capacity). If you need to change the limit, you can change it using this command: (New-CSOnlinePSTNGW, parameter -Capacity).
_Mgmt.DirectRouting.ConcurrentCallCapaci: 'How to fix' text for when concurrent call% of trunk reaches 100%, where {maxConcurrentCallLimit} is maximum concurrent call limit set by tenant admin.
Mgmt.DirectRouting.ConcurrentCallCapacit: Each trunk has a limit of calls it can handle at a time. The current limit is {maxConcurrentCallLimit}. Over the last 24 hours, we saw attempts to make more calls than the current limit. Consider adding capacity to your Session Border Controller (SBC) or adding additional SBCs to the route. Note: We don’t measure real-time volume on SBC. Instead, we calculate the number of concurrent calls based on statistics from the last 4 hours and compare it to the number configured during the pairing (New-CSOnlinePSTNGW, parameter -Capacity). If you need to change the limit, you can change it using this command: (New-CSOnlinePSTNGW, parameter -Capacity).
_Mgmt.DirectRouting.ConcurrentCallCapaci: 'How to fix' text for when max concurrent call of trunk is not set by tenant admin.
Mgmt.DirectRouting.ConcurrentCallCapacit: Each trunk has a limit of calls it can handle at a time. If the number of calls is higher than the limit, you may get dropped calls. To change this limit, use this command: Set-CSOnlinePSTNGateway. To get detailed instructions, run “Help Set-CSOnlinePSTNGateway -Detailed.” Once you set this limit, we’ll notify you when your trunk approaches or exceeds capacity. Note: We don’t measure real-time volume on SBC. Instead, we calculate the number of concurrent calls based on statistics from the last 4 hours and compare it to the number configured during the pairing (New-CSOnlinePSTNGW, parameter -Capacity).
_Mgmt.DirectRouting.TLSCertExpiry.HowToF: 'How to fix' text for TLS connectivity when certificate will expiry within 30 days, where {certExpiryDate} is certificate expiry date.
Mgmt.DirectRouting.TLSCertExpiry.HowToFi: The certificate for this trunk expires on {certExpiryDate}. After the certificate expires, the trunk won’t be able to connect to the Office 365. Renew the certificate now to avoid any service interruption.
_Mgmt.DirectRouting.TLSCertExpired.HowTo: 'How to fix' text for TLS connectivity when certificate is expired.
Mgmt.DirectRouting.TLSCertExpired.HowToF: You can't use the trunk as the certificate has expired. Please renew the certificate to continue using the trunk.
_Mgmt.DirectRouting.TLSInactive.HowToFix: 'How to fix' text for TLS connectivity when the SBC did not send TLS handhsake in last 15 min.
Mgmt.DirectRouting.TLSInactive.HowToFix: We monitor trunk connectivity every 15 sec by using Transport Layer Security (TLS) handshake, along with SIP Options monitoring. This trunk hasn’t attempted a TLS handshake in the last 15 minutes. To troubleshoot and fix: Check your Session Border Controller (SBC) certificate validity; check the trunk availability; check your network environment and firewall; and make sure that sending SIP options on the trunk is turned on.
_Mgmt.DirectRouting.SIPNoData.HowToFix.c: 'How to fix' text for SIP options monitoring when the SBC did not reply on SIP option request.
Mgmt.DirectRouting.SIPNoData.HowToFix: We rely on SIP options sent by the trunk to monitor the connection and ability of the trunk to process SIP traffic. This trunk hasn’t sent SIP options in the last 15 minutes. Check the availability of the trunk and make sure that sending SIP options and the trunk is turned on.
_Mgmt.DirectRouting.SIPWarningNotConfigu: 'How to fix' text for SIP options monitoring when the tenant admin didn't configure SIP options during the pairing.
Mgmt.DirectRouting.SIPWarningNotConfigur: Trunk monitoring using SIP options isn’t turned on. Microsoft Calling System uses SIP Options and Transport Layer Security (TLS) handshake monitoring to detect the health of the connected Session Border Controllers (SBCs) at the application level. You’ll have problems if this trunk can be reached at the network level (by ping) but the certificate has expired or the SIP stack doesn’t work. To help identify such problems early, we recommend enabling sending SIP options. Check your SBC manufacturer documentation to configure sending SIP options.
_Mgmt.DirectRouting.SIPWarningDisabled.H: 'How to fix' text for SIP options monitoring when the tenant admin disabled SIP options during the pairing.
Mgmt.DirectRouting.SIPWarningDisabled.Ho: The trunk was paired to Direct Routing but is in a "Disabled" state. When you pair a trunk using the New-CSOnlinePSTNGateway command, the trunk is disabled by default unless you explicitly enabled it using this parameter: Enable $true. Please check the status of the gateway and make sure it’s enabled.

Mgmt.DirectRouting.SIPWarningPingError.H: The Session Border Controller exists in our database (your administrator created it using the command New-CSOnlinePSTNGateway). But we have difficulties determining SIP Options status. Please check in 15 minutes.
_Mgmt.DirectRouting.WarningPingExpired.H: 'How to fix' text for SIP options monitoring when ping expired.
Mgmt.DirectRouting.SIPWarningPingExpired: The Session Border Controller exists in our database (your administrator created it using the command New-CSOnlinePSTNGateway) and was sending SIP option. But we didn't receive any SIP options in last 15 minutes.
_Mgmt.DirectRouting.SIPWarningNoData.How: 'How to fix' text for SIP options monitoring when there is no data.
Mgmt.DirectRouting.SIPWarningNoData.HowT: The Session Border Controller exists in our database (your administrator created it using the command New-CSOnlinePSTNGateway). It is configured to send SIP options but we never saw the SIP options coming back from this SBC.
_Mgmt.DirectRouting.TrunkStatusNoData.Ho: 'How to fix' text for trunk status when there is no data related to that trunk.
Mgmt.DirectRouting.TrunkStatusNoData.How: The Session Border Controller (SBC) exists in our database (your administrator created it using the command New-CSOnlinePSTNGateway), but we haven't received any connections attempts from this SBC. Check the configuration on this SBC.
_Mgmt.DirectRouting.TrunkStatusInactiveN: 'How to fix' text for trunk status when the trunk doesn't have any recent calls.
Mgmt.DirectRouting.TrunkStatusInactiveNo: This Session Border Controller (SBC) hasn’t sent or received any calls in the last 24 hours. We do see SIP options flowing between Direct Routing and the SBC, which could indicate a problem. If the SBC shouldn’t send or receive calls, you can ignore this warning.
_Mgmt.DirectRouting.TrunkStatusInactiveN: 'How to fix' text for trunk status when the trunk doesn't have any recent ping.
Mgmt.DirectRouting.TrunkStatusInactiveNo: This Session Border Controller (SBC) hasn’t sent or received any calls in the last 24 hours. We recommend turning on SIP Options monitoring, which lets you know whether the SBC is functional. Check the configuration of the SBC, your network, and firewall.
_Mgmt.DirectRouting.TrunkStatusInactiveN: 'How to fix' text for trunk status when the trunk doesn't have any recent ping or call.
Mgmt.DirectRouting.TrunkStatusInactiveNo: This Session Border Controller (SBC) hasn’t sent any SIP Options, and it hasn’t sent or received any calls in the last 24 hours. Regardless of whether you’ve turned on calling via this SBC, we recommend turning on SIP Options monitoring, which lets you know whether the SBC is functional. Check the configuration of your SBC, network, and firewall, and make sure that SIP Options are flowing.

Mgmt.DirectRouting.NERIssues.Issue: The Network Effectiveness Ratio is below 90%.

_Mgmt.DirectRouting.NERIssues.HowToFix.c: 'How to fix' text for network effectiveness (NER) when NER has issues.
Mgmt.DirectRouting.NERIssues.HowToFix: Network Effectiveness Ratio (NER) is the ITU-T recommended parameter to measure the ability of the network to deliver calls. It’s calculated based on this formula: 𝑁𝐸𝑅=𝐴𝑛𝑠𝑤𝑒𝑟𝑒𝑑 𝑐𝑎𝑙𝑙𝑠+𝑈𝑠𝑒𝑟 𝐵𝑢𝑠𝑦+𝑅𝑖𝑛𝑔 𝑛𝑜 𝐴𝑛𝑠𝑤𝑒𝑟+𝑇𝑒𝑟𝑚𝑖𝑛𝑎𝑙 𝑅𝑒𝑗𝑒𝑐𝑡𝑆𝑒𝑖𝑧𝑢𝑟𝑒𝑠𝑥100. The ratio calculates how many calls were delivered. It ignores user errors, such as unanswered or rejected calls. If the value goes down, your network may have a problem you need to investigate. Factors that could decrease the NER: network problems, firewall rules, insufficient bandwidth. To troubleshoot a low NER value, use the Call Quality Dashboard to analyze your network. In particular, check mid-call failures.
_Mgmt.DirectRouting.ACDIssues.HowToFix.c: 'How to fix' text for average call duration (ACD) when ACD has issues.
Mgmt.DirectRouting.ACDIssues.HowToFix: Average Call Duration (ACD) is a good indicator of the quality of the end user experience. Decreased Average Call Duration often indicates problems with call quality (such as noise, glitches, delays, and mid-call failures). When users have call-quality problems, they often redial a number several times, or after a short call switch to a mobile device. For low ACD, use the Call Quality Dashboard to analyze these network parameters: Latency (RTT), Burst Packet Loss, Packet Loss, Packet inter-arrival Jitter, and Packet reorder. You can also analyze mid-call failures by using the Call Quality Dashboard (filter by trunk and mid-call failures reasons).
_Mgmt.DirectRouting.RoundTripIssues.HowT: 'How to fix' text for round trip when round trip has issues.
Mgmt.DirectRouting.RoundTripIssues.HowTo: Round Trip latency is the length of time it takes for a packet to be sent, plus length of time it takes for an acknowledgment that the packet was received. This parameter is very important when transmitting real-time audio. If packets arrive too late, there will be delays in audio streams. The recommended value is less than 100 ms. To learn more about network requirements for audio and how to troubleshoot problems, read this article: https://docs.microsoft.com/SkypeForBusiness/optimizing-your-network/media-quality-and-network-connectivity-performance.
_Mgmt.DirectRouting.PacketLossIssues.How: 'How to fix' text for packet loss when packet loss has issues.
Mgmt.DirectRouting.PacketLossIssues.HowT: Packet loss tells you how many packets failed to reach the final destination. When transmitting real time traffic over a network, you want to minimize the number of packets lost during transmission. High packet loss usually degrades audio quality (glitches, distorted audio). For best audio quality, the packet loss value should be less than 1%.
_Mgmt.DirectRouting.JitterIssues.HowToFi: 'How to fix' text for jitter when jitter has issues.
Mgmt.DirectRouting.JitterIssues.HowToFix: Jitter measures differences between the arrival time of packets to the Microsoft Calling system from the trunk. For best call quality, you want a constant flow of packets (low jitter). If packets arrive with a significant difference (high jitter), the codec can’t produce a continuous audio stream and users might notice delays. For best audio quality, jitter should be less than 30 ms.
_Mgmt.DirectRouting.NetworkParameterAddi: Link for additonal link in 'How to fix' text for network parameters, where {link} is link string with hyper link.
Mgmt.DirectRouting.NetworkParameterAddit: To learn more about network requirements for transmitting audio and how to troubleshoot problems, read this article: {link}.

Mgmt.PhoneNumbers.PortingWizard.Error.Ap: Number '{InvalidTelephoneNumber}' on line {LineNumber} isn't an E.164-compliant number. Please fix the format of the number. If you continue to have problems, contact {PSTNServiceDeskLink}.
_Mgmt.PhoneNumbers.PortingWizard.Error.A: Mapping for TNM Porting API error no. 11002 TelephoneNumbersExceedMaxAllowed (when user tries to upload more TNs then accepted. {MaxAmount} and {Amount} are numbers). {PSTNServiceDeskLink} is link to the PSTN support desk.
Mgmt.PhoneNumbers.PortingWizard.Error.Ap: You can't submit an order with more than {MaxAmount} phone numbers. You have submitted {Amount} numbers. Please remove some numbers and try again. If you continue to have problems, contact {PSTNServiceDeskLink}.

Mgmt.PhoneNumbers.PortingWizard.Error.Ap: The number or numbers {InvalidTelephoneNumbers} don't belong to {Region} as the country or region you have selected. Please remove them and try again. If you continue to have problems, contact {PSTNServiceDeskLink}.
_Mgmt.PhoneNumbers.PortingWizard.Error.A: Mapping for TNM Porting API error no. 11004 ActionNotAllowedInCurrentOrderStatus (User tries to do porting in wrong flow). {Action} is an actin that user tries to do, {CurrentStatus} is current status of porting order. {PSTNServiceDeskLink} is link to the PSTN support desk.
Mgmt.PhoneNumbers.PortingWizard.Error.Ap: We can't perform action '{Action}' in current status '{CurrentStatus}'. If you continue to have problems, contact {PSTNServiceDeskLink}.
_Mgmt.PhoneNumbers.PortingWizard.Error.A: Mapping for TNM Porting API error no. 11005 AttachmentContainsNoPhoneNumbers (User tries to upload CSV without TNs). {TnsFileName} is name of the file user sent. {PSTNServiceDeskLink} is link to the PSTN support desk.

Mgmt.PhoneNumbers.PortingWizard.Error.Ap: We don't support porting this number or numbers: {TelephoneNumbers}. Please remove them and try again. If you continue to have problems, contact {PSTNServiceDeskLink}.
_Mgmt.PhoneNumbers.PortingWizard.Error.A: Mapping for TNM Porting API error no. 11009 UnableToPortFromLosingTelco. _Mgmt.PhoneNumbers.PortingWizard.Error.A: Mapping for TNM Porting API error no. 11012 RequestedFOCDateCannotBeInThePast. Error can happen during TNM Porting order Creation. {FocDate} is localized date string. {PSTNServiceDeskLink} is link to the PSTN support desk.

_Mgmt.PhoneNumbers.PortingWizard.Error.A: Mapping for TNM Porting API error no. 11013 AccountNumberAndPinRequired. Error can happen during TNM Porting order Creation. {PSTNServiceDeskLink} is link to the PSTN support desk.

_Mgmt.PhoneNumbers.PortingWizard.Error.A: Mapping for TNM Porting API error no. 11014 RequestedFOCDateIsTooFarInFuture. Error can happen during TNM Porting order Submit. {FocDate} is localized date string. {PSTNServiceDeskLink} is link to the PSTN support desk.
Mgmt.PhoneNumbers.PortingWizard.Error.Ap: The date you requested ({FocDate}) is too far in the future. Please choose a date sooner and try again. If you continue to have problems, contact {PSTNServiceDeskLink}.
_Mgmt.PhoneNumbers.PortingWizard.Error.A: Mapping for TNM Porting API error no. 11015 RequestedTimeIsOutsideOfBusinessHours. Error can happen during TNM Porting order Submit. {FocDateTime} is localized date with time string. {PSTNServiceDeskLink} is link to the PSTN support desk.
Mgmt.PhoneNumbers.PortingWizard.Error.Ap: The date and time you requested ({FocDateTime}) isn't available. Please choose a different date and time and try again. If you continue to have problems, contact {PSTNServiceDeskLink}.
_Mgmt.PhoneNumbers.PortingWizard.Error.A: Mapping for TNM Porting API error no. 11016 DateSpecifiedIsDuringWeekendOrHoliday. Error can happen during TNM Porting order Submit. {FocDate} is localized date string. {PSTNServiceDeskLink} is link to the PSTN support desk.

_Mgmt.PhoneNumbers.PortingWizard.Error.A: Mapping for TNM Porting API error no. 11017 InputExceedsMaxLength. Error can happen during TNM Porting order Creation. {FieldName} is localized field name, {MaxAmount} and {Length} are numbers. {PSTNServiceDeskLink} is link to the PSTN support desk.

_Mgmt.PhoneNumbers.PortingWizard.Error.A: Mapping for TNM Porting API error no. 11019 InvalidPinNumber. Error can happen during TNM Porting order Submit. {PSTNServiceDeskLink} is link to the PSTN support desk.

Mgmt.TeamsMeetingPolicy.Form.Fields.Medi: This setting determines the media bit rate for audio, video, and video-based app sharing in meetings for people in your organization. This setting gives you granular control over managing bandwidth in your organization. Depending on the meetings scenario, we recommend to have enough bandwidth in place for a good quality experience. The minimum value is 30 Kbps and the maximum value depends on the meeting scenario. For meetings that need the highest quality video experience, such as CEO board meetings and Teams live events, we recommend you set the bandwidth to 10 Mbps.

Mgmt.TeamsCallingLineIdPolicy.List.PageD: Caller ID policies are used to change or block the Caller ID (also called a Calling Line ID) for users. By default, the user's phone number is displayed when a call is made to a PSTN phone number such as a landline or mobile phone. Mgmt.Locations.ReportingLabel.PageDescri: Reporting labels are used to give an IP subnet a name that links it to a physical location such as offices, buildings, or organizational sites within your organization. They are used by Call Analytics to make it easier to see a name of a place instead of just an IP subnet in reports. You can upload a CSV or TSV that has a list of physical locations and their associated network subnets. {link}

Mgmt.Locations.EmergencyAddresses.PageDe: Emergency address is a civic address which is a physical street address of a place of business for your organization. An emergency location is a civic address with an optional place. If your business has more than one physical location, it's likely that you'll need more than one emergency location. {link}

_Mgmt.NetworkPlanner.NetworkSettingsForm: PSTN Egress Label Tooltip
Select one of these options to define how users can make calls out to the PSTN. The PSTN is the public telephone network and contains mobile and landline dedicated phone numbers. {learnMoreLink}
_Mgmt.NetworkPlanner.NetworkSettingsForm: Express Route Label Tooltip
If you are using ExpressRoute on your network, turn this on. With ExpressRoute, you can create private connections between Office 365 datacenters and your private networks. ExpressRoute connections don't go over the public Internet, and offer more reliability, faster speeds, lower latencies, and higher security than typical Internet connections. {link}
_Mgmt.NetworkPlanner.NetworkSettingsForm: Connected To WAN Label Tooltip
If your network is connected to a service provider that gives you an Internet connection, turn this on. When you turn it on you will need to provide the speed of that connection to the Internet and then put in the WAN audio and video queue sizes. {learnMoreLink}
_Mgmt.NetworkPlanner.NetworkSettingsForm: Internet Link Capacity Label Tooltip
This is the device that connects this network site to the Internet. For small business, this would be the speed of the service that connects to the Internet. In larger networks, this will mostly likely be a dedicated connection.
